## 2. Nginx Reverse Proxy Configuration

Nginx was configured as a reverse proxy to provide HTTPS access to TheHive and MISP on separate ports.

**Final working nginx.conf:**

```nginx
# THEHIVE PROXY
server {
    listen 443 ssl default_server;
    server_name _;

    ssl_certificate     /etc/nginx/ssl/thehive.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/thehive.key;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://thehive:9000;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Connection "";
    }
}

# MISP PROXY
server {
    listen 444 ssl default_server;
    server_name _;

    ssl_certificate     /etc/nginx/ssl/thehive.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/thehive.key;

    location / {
        proxy_pass https://misp.local:443;
        proxy_set_header Host $host:444;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
        proxy_ssl_verify off;
        proxy_redirect https://10.0.11.22/ https://10.0.11.22:444/;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Connection "";
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `server_name _;` matches any hostname including bare IPs
- `default_server` ensures correct routing by port
- TheHive is proxied over HTTP internally (port 9000)
- MISP is proxied over HTTPS internally (port 443) as the MISP container handles its own SSL
- `proxy_http_version 1.1` is required to support chunked responses from TheHive 5

**Access URLs:**
- TheHive: `https://10.0.11.22`
- MISP: `https://10.0.11.22:444`
- Cortex: `http://10.0.11.22:9001`

