## 3. SSL Certificate Generation

A self-signed SSL certificate was generated with the server's public IP as the Subject Alternative Name (SAN), which is required for external connections:

```bash
openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048 \
  -keyout ~/docker-compose/ssl/thehive.key \
  -out ~/docker-compose/ssl/thehive.crt \
  -subj "/CN=51.52.158.142" \
  -addext "subjectAltName=IP:51.52.158.142,IP:10.0.11.22"
```

> **Important:** The certificate must include the public IP as a SAN. A certificate issued only for `localhost` or the internal IP will fail SSL verification from external hosts like Splunk.

