## 4. Splunk Integration – TA-TheHive-Cortex

### 4.1 Install the App

Install **TA-TheHive-Cortex** (version 3.9.0) from Splunkbase:
```
https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/5401
```

Also install the **Splunk Common Information Model (CIM)** app as a required dependency:
```
https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/1621
```

### 4.2 Fix Deprecated Password API

The app uses a deprecated Splunk password API that causes the UI to fail on newer versions of Splunk Enterprise. Patch it directly:

```bash
sed -i 's/_get_all_passwords()/get_clear_passwords_in_realm()/g' \
  /opt/splunk/etc/apps/TA-thehive-cortex/bin/ta_thehive_cortex/aob_py3/splunktaucclib/rest_handler/credentials.py
```

Restart Splunk after patching:
```bash
/opt/splunk/bin/splunk restart
```

### 4.3 Create the Instances Lookup

The app uses a CSV lookup to store instance configuration. Create the lookup directory and file:

```bash
mkdir -p /opt/splunk/etc/apps/TA-thehive-cortex/lookups

cat > /opt/splunk/etc/apps/TA-thehive-cortex/lookups/thehive_cortex_instances.csv << 'EOF'
id,type,organisation,host,port,uri,authentication_type,account_name,verify_cert,client_cert,proxy_url,proxy_account
Production_TheHive,TheHive5,LJT Systems,51.52.158.142,443,/,api_key,TheHive_Admin,0,-,-,-
EOF
```

Register the lookup definition:
```bash
cat > /opt/splunk/etc/apps/TA-thehive-cortex/local/transforms.conf << 'EOF'
[thehive_cortex_instances]
filename = thehive_cortex_instances.csv
EOF
```

### 4.4 Configure the Account

Generate an API key in TheHive:
1. Log into TheHive → click your username (top right)
2. Go to **Settings → API Key → Create**
3. Copy the key

Add the account to the app config:
```bash
cat >> /opt/splunk/etc/apps/TA-thehive-cortex/local/ta_thehive_cortex_account.conf << 'EOF'

[TheHive_Admin]
username = apikey
password = YOUR_THEHIVE_API_KEY_HERE
EOF
```

### 4.5 Add the SSL Certificate to the App's CA Bundle

Append the self-signed certificate to the app's certifi bundle so Splunk can verify the connection:

```bash
cat >> /opt/splunk/etc/apps/TA-thehive-cortex/bin/ta_thehive_cortex/aob_py3/certifi/cacert.pem << 'EOF'
-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
<PASTE YOUR thehive.crt CONTENT HERE>
-----END CERTIFICATE-----
EOF
```

Restart Splunk:
```bash
/opt/splunk/bin/splunk restart
```

### 4.6 Firewall Rules

Ensure the following ports are open on the Docker host firewall:
- **443** – TheHive (inbound from Splunk IP)
- **444** – MISP (inbound from browser)

Port 9000 (TheHive internal) should **not** be exposed externally as nginx handles all external traffic on 443.

